### Baloo Acceleration

3.1 Consumer Shopping Ads remain paused in the US with no ETA to dial back up: 

Following Amazon's pause of all WW Google Shopping Ads in July 2025, WW excluding US was re-enabled in mid-August (week 33). Central Stores has confirmed there are no plans to reverse the US pause, with the expectation that US Shopping Ads will remain offline through 2026. This decision blocks our US launch plans due to our reliance on the centrally-provided Shopping data feed, which is intentionally blocked from Google. The US represents 67% of Consumer iOPS (Q1–Q3 2025), making this pause particularly impactful to our growth trajectory. The next largest opportunity is the UK, which drives 10% of Consumer iOPS.

Given these constraints, we have two paths forward: pursue a WW ex-US launch with an initial focus on UK-only ($14–23MM opportunity) and planned scale in 2027 ($88MM WW ex-US opportunity), or develop Baloo support for alternate (non-Shopping Ads) channels ($1.26B opportunity). A UK-only launch maintains parity with planned resource commitment from Tech and Marketing, as launching a single country requires the same level of support. However, expanding beyond UK to additional geographies would require scaled investment across Tech for integration of central feeds, creation of supplemental feeds, and OCI setup and value development, as well as Marketing for additional headcount to support multi-market management and operations. Expansion to additional geographies is recommended to follow in 2027 once operational efficiency is established. Alternatively, expanding Baloo support beyond Paid Search/Shopping Ads to additional channels (onsite, email, and MCS) diversifies our acquisition approach, increases opportunities for success, and enables richer customer experiences across a broader set of touchpoints. 


