WW:  Paid Search delivered 63.6K registrations in Feb (+9% vs. OP2), driven by strong performance in the US (+16.4% vs. OP2) and EU5 (+4.6% vs. OP2). US performance was supported by +26% YoY Brand traffic growth and Non-Brand CPA improvement from bidding portfolio consolidation to better leverage OCI bidding. EU5 achieved OP2 through OCI tailwinds in UK, with strategic budget reallocation from DE to FRITES, enabling OP2 achievement in FRES while driving higher overall registrations at the EU5 level. CA (+18.5% vs. OP2) continued benefit from Jan mobile landing page optimization, driving -29% CPA improvement. JP missed OP2 by -47.5%, as the Ministry of Health ended on Jan.31st with no carryover impact in Feb as anticipated and landed traffic remaining below expectations.

US: US delivered 32.9K registrations (+16% vs. OP2, +68% YoY) with spend of $2.7M and CPA of $83. Both Brand (+13% vs. OP2) and Non-Brand (+18% vs. OP2) achieved OP2 plan in Feb. Brand performance was supported by continued 26%+ traffic growth YoY, though increased competition from Walmart – with its impression share rising from 43% to 54% - drove CPC up from $2.5 to $2.8, contributing to a MoM Brand CPA increase from $65 to $77. Non-Brand CPA improvement was driven by Q4'25 bidding portfolio consolidation to better leverage OCI bidding. To maximize US iECCP, we overspent by +6% ($154K) in Feb. Performance was unstable in the first two weeks of the month, leading to elevated Non-Brand CPA (+21% MoM). Optimizations were implemented and CPA was brought back down. We will further consolidate campaigns in Mar with a stronger overall management structure for US Paid Search. YoY PS US remains strong at +67% growth, with Brand up 19% and Non-Brand more than doubling YoY.

EU: In February, EU5 delivered 24K registrations (+5% vs OP2, +16% YoY) with $1.8M spend (+3% vs OP2 spend). OP2 was hit in February due to strong performance in UK (+24% OP2) after OCI implementation and strategically reallocating budget to non OCI regions to ensure we hit OP2.
UK surpassed OP2 by 24%, despite spend decreasing 6% vs OP2, generated by 1) OCI implementation and 2) increased Brand performance due to a 33% YOY increase in Brand traffic, which helped offset overall EU5 performance. FR and ES both achieved OP2, +1% and +10% respectively, generated by greater investment vs, +14% for FR and +16% for ES vs OP2 spend, which will continue until OCI implementation in Q2.
DE missed OP2 by 4%, due to NB performance, with DE NB OP2 regs at -22% vs other OCI region UK NB OP2 regs at +18%, generated by NB performance decreasing -16% YoY, reflecting stronger Y25 DE NB performance than the UK, which created a higher baseline for OP2 projections. IT was short of OP2 by 1%, reflecting lower investment vs other non OCI regions, with +1% OP2 spend versus +5% EU2 OP2 spend. This reflects our team's proactive adjustment to reallocate budget to non OCI regions as well as avoiding high overspend while resolving the Italy VAT 22% tax, which was resolved by end of Feb. The team is implementing landing page optimization in March for EU5 to tackle NB CVR while awaiting OCI implementation for EU3.


CA: continue to see good CPA from Jan LP optimization. work w/CA team explore on agency service. 

In February, CA delivered 2.8K registrations (+18.5% vs OP2, +32.3% YoY) with spend of $207K (-0.9% vs OP2, -5.9% YoY) at a CPA of $73, maintaining the strong CPA range from January and continuing to benefit from the January LP optimization on Non-Brand. The PS team is also working with the CA team to support their Agency Service collaboration (in progress).
YoY., the spend penetration ratio shifted from 28:72 in 2025 to 50:50 in 2026, as Brand spend reallocation drove greater efficiency. Reduced demand from tariff impact beginning in Wk6 of February 2025 also contributed to the favorable YoY comparison. The 39.6% YoY increase in Brand registrations was driven by a corresponding 35.6% rise in traffic, while the 20.4% YoY increase in Non-Brand registrations was driven by a 45% reduction in CPAs YoY.

JP: MHLW ends on 1/31 and don’t have carry over as expected. Overall traffic is down 11.8% YoY, resulted in missing Feb goal -47.5% and but still +61.6% QTD. 

JP delivered 1.6K registrations in February (-47.5% vs OP2, -1.2% YoY) with spend of $121K (-12.9% vs OP2, -0.5% YoY) and CPA of $78, as search demand declined and February carry-over volume came in below expectations following the MHLW period end on 1/31. Pacing budgets were adjusted mid-February to reallocate toward Non-Brand testing across Google and Yahoo in March. Overall Traffic is -11.8% YoY, with Brand Plus seeing a 56% decline in traffic and Brand Core CPCs up 50% YoY, shifting the Brand Core:Plus ratio from 81:19 in 2025 to 91:9 in 2026. Despite this, JP requires only 28.6% of OP2 total registrations in March to achieve the Q1'26 OP2 goal.  YoY brand core traffic down -0.7% , remains below expectations.

AU: AU delivered 1.1K registrations in February (-1% vs. OP2) with $159K spend (+8% vs. OP2) Registrations decreased slightly, -3% MoM, primarily due to a 27% increase in NB CPA. We agreed to target a $140 CPA with the Australia team each month, and rather than seeing an increase in regs, we saw an increase in inefficiency. We are leaning into creating more efficiency for NB by implementing Adobe bid strategies to more closely optimize towards registrations, but will keep an eye on this to avoid increases to CPC alone.

MX: MX delivered 1.1K registrations in February (+32% vs. OP2, +37% YoY) with $68K spend (+28% vs. OP2, -44% YoY). YoY growth can be attributed to +112% YoY Brand registrations, which increased because of a 59% increase in traffic YoY as well as +33% CVR YoY. The efficiency on NB side was necessitated by the market’s significant decrease in budget to meet our new ie%CCP target of 100% mid-last year.


